{{Coord|35.667585|N|139.745064|E|display=title}}
{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Japan Oil, Gas and Metals National Corporation |nativename = 独立行政法人石油天然ガス・金属鉱物資源機構 |logo = JOGMEC logo.jpg |logo_width = |logo_caption = Logo of the Japan Oil, Gas and Metals National Corporation. |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |formed = February 29, 2004 |jurisdiction = [[Japan]] |headquarters = [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]] |employees = 475 (as of April 1, 2012) |budget = 1,564 Billion Yen (2010 Fiscal Year) |chief1_name = [[President (corporate title)|President]] |chief1_position = Tetsuhiro Hosono |website = [http://www.jogmec.go.jp/ http://www.jogmec.go.jp/] }}
The {{Nihongo|'''Japan Oil, Gas and Metals National Corporation'''|独立行政法人石油天然ガス・金属鉱物資源機構|Sekiyu ten'nen gasu kinzoku kōbutsu shigen kikō|'''JOGMEC'''}}, is a Japanese government [[Independent Administrative Institution]] which was created in 2004 when the former Japan National Oil Corporation merged with the former Metal Mining Agency of Japan.<ref name="about1">[http://www.jogmec.go.jp/english/index.html Japan Oil, Gas and Metals National Corporation] (JOGMEC): [http://www.jogmec.go.jp/english/aboutus/index.html About us, overview].</ref>
==History== JOGMEC integrates corollary functions in one administrative entity. The former Japan National Oil Corporation (JNOC) had been tasked with securing a stable supply of [[oil]] and [[natural gas]] for Japan's use. The former [[Metal]] Mining Agency of Japan (MMAJ) had been tasked with ensuring a stable supply of [[nonferrous]] metal and [[mineral]] resources for Japan's use. Greater efficiencies were realized by combining two bureaucracies with similar missions{{Citation needed|date=January 2012}}. JOGMEC was established in 2004 pursuant to the 2002 Law Concerning the Japan Oil, Gas and Metals National Corporation.<ref>JOGMEC: [http://www.jogmec.go.jp/english/aboutus/history.html About us, history].</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jogmec.go.jp/english/aboutus/docs/jogmec_law_2005.pdf |title=Japan Oil, Gas and Metals National Corporation |publisher=JOGMEC |date= |accessdate=2018-07-11}}</ref>
In March 2013, JOGMEC becomes the first to successfully extract [[Methane clathrate|methane hydrate]] from [[seabed]] deposits.<ref>https://www.reuters.com/article/2013/03/12/us-methane-hydrates-japan-idUSBRE92B07620130312</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=By HIROKO TABUCHIMARCH 12, 2013 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/03/13/business/global/japan-says-it-is-first-to-tap-methane-hydrate-deposit.html |title=An Energy Coup for Japan: ‘Flammable Ice’ - The New York Times |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=2013-03-12 |accessdate=2018-07-11}}</ref>
==Activities== JOGMEC's Geological Remote Satellite Sensing Centre in [[Lobatse]], [[Botswana]] was created in partnership with the southern African nation's Department of Geological Survey in July 2008. The Japan-Botswana partnership will work together in developing the exploration of minerals through methods such as [[remote sensing]].<ref>Botswana Press Agency (BOPA): [http://www.gov.bw/cgi-bin/news.cgi?d=20090324&i=Geological_satellite_centre_welcome "Geological satellite centre welcome."] March 24, 2009.</ref>
JOGMEC manages rare metal stockpiles in conjunction with private companies.<ref>National Research Council (US). (2008). [https://books.google.com/books?id=d_huh50jmnoC&pg=PA186&dq=jogmec&ei=K73KSeeaNqDCM6bT-cEE ''Minerals, Critical Minerals, and the U.S. Economy,'' p. 186.]</ref>
